The paper deals with distributed algorithms for leader election in multi-hop radio networks, which are typically studied in the field of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also involves analysis of the time complexity of the algorithms, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The use of randomized algorithms and information theory concepts suggests a possible fit under cs.IT. Finally, the paper presents improvements over previous algorithms, which could be considered as a form of system optimization (cs.SI).
